        "version": "0.0.1",
        "description": "\n# End-to-End Lifecycle of an API Key in Pylon\n\nThe mobile app being deployed to the App Store contains an API key from Pylon in its environment. Customers installing the app only provide their `company_id` \u2014 the app uses the API key silently in the background to determine the app calling the api and the `company_id` to load custom configurations for the customer.\n\n\n## Phase 1 \u2014 Provisioning (Internal)\n\nThis happens when:\n- A new app is onboarded (e.g., ESS, Membership Portal, etc.)\n\n### Step 1: Generate the Key\n\nYou (or an admin panel) run:\n\n```php\n$service->generate(\n    'Kinetic Technology Limited',  // name/description\n    'ESS',                          // app_name\n    ['config:read']                 // scopes\n);\n```\n\nWhat the System does:\n\n1. Generates key with format `pyl_{appName}_{random}`\n2. Hashes it with SHA256\n3. Stores only the hash\n4. Returns raw key ONCE\n\nExample raw key:\n\n```\npyl_ESS_83js9dk29sks92ks0sks...\n```\n\n## Phase 2 \u2014 Embedded in Your App\n\nThe API key is compiled into the mobile app's .env. End customers never see it.\n\n```env\n# Your app's environment file\nPYLON_API_KEY=pyl_ESS_83js9dk29sks92ks0sks...\n```\n\nWhen a customer launches the app and enters their company ID, a request is made to the API with the API key and company ID:\n\n```http\nPOST /api/config\nContent-Type: application/json\nX-API-KEY: pyl_ESS_83js9dk29sks92ks0sks...\n\n{\n  \"company_id\": \"a5ab3645-b95c-ec11-8f6f-0666489d8ee3\"\n}\n```\n\n## Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"company_id\": \"a5ab3645-b95c-ec11-8f6f-0666489d8ee3\",\n  \"branding\": {\n    \"name\": \"Kinetic Technology Limited\",\n    \"primary_color\": \"#FFA500\",\n    \"logo_url\": \"https://kinetics.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/KTL-Logo-1.png\"\n  },\n  \"api\": {\n    \"base_url\": \"https://api.platform.example.com\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## What Happens on Every Request\n\n1. App sends request with embedded API key + customer-provided `company_id`\n2. Middleware reads `X-API-KEY`\n3. Validates:\n   - Key exists\n   - Key is active\n4. Controller uses `company_id` from request body to return company-specific config\n"
    },
